# List of heritage sites in Wynberg, Cape Town

This is a list of the heritage sites in Wynberg Magisterial District in Cape Town, as recognized by the South African Heritage Resources Agency.
Beyond Newlands lies the suburb of Claremont. The Herschel monument stands in Grove Avenue on what was formerly the Feldhausen property.
Sir John F. W. Herschel (1792-1871) was a famous British astronomer, the only son of an equally famous astronomer, Sir William Herschel. He came to the Cape in January, 1834, to make astronomical observations. He went to live at Claremont and stayed there until March, 1838.
Type of site: School.
